=== Intel case ===

In July 1995, Schwartz was prosecuted in the case of ''State of Oregon vs. Randal Schwartz'', which dealt with compromised computer security during his time as a system administrator for [[Intel]]. In the process of performing [[penetration testing]], he cracked a number of passwords on Intel's systems.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news
 |title=Technology: On the net; An Intel computer security expert runs afoul of the law. So much for the 'hacker ethic'?
